  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 35 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 14 critical, 7 high, 12 medium, 6 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB); plus 18 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, cold‑temperature performance penalties and mist  — most notably around Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Sofia (SOF/LBSF). Network hotspots: Almaty (ALA/UAAA), Sofia (SOF/LBSF), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and 30 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Sofia (SOF/LBSF), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and 9 others.",
